author: David Scott
title: Joey Logano wins Charlotte race, clinches spot in 3rd round of Chase
text:
Joey Logano wins Charlotte race, clinches spot in 3rd round of Chase David Scott The Charlotte Observer 
CONCORD, N.C. _ Joey Logano dominated Sunday at Charlotte Motor Speedway, winning the Bank of America 500 and clinching a spot in the third round of NASCAR's Chase.tmpplchld Logano's victory, coming in the first race of the playoffs' second round, was his first in 14 career races at Charlotte.tmpplchld "This helps us sleep the next couple of weeks," Logano said.tmpplchld Kevin Harvick finished second _ his 11th runner-up finish of the season. Martin Truex Jr. was third and Denny Hamlin. Austin Dillon was the only non-Chase driver in the top 10, finishing seventh.tmpplchld The race _ postponed by rain from Saturday night _ was tough on the Chase ambitions of three drivers. Kyle Busch, after a wreck with Kyle Larson entering pit road, was 20th. Dale Earnhardt Jr. was 28th and pole-winner Matt Kenseth 42nd.tmpplchld The top eight from the second round advance to the third round. The second race of the Chase's second round is next Sunday at Kansas Speedway.tmpplchld ___tmpplchld (c)2015 The Charlotte Observer (Charlotte, N.C.)tmpplchld Visit The Charlotte Observer (Charlotte, N.C.) at www.charlotteobserver.comtmpplchld Distributed by Tribune Content Agency, LLC.tmpplchld
